Appendix D: Implementation Code (Python)

Below are core code snippets illustrating the implementation of the computational pipeline. The code is modular and follows the architecture described. All functions are documented.

D.1 ECG Preprocessing and HRV Extraction

```python
import numpy as np
from scipy.signal import butter, filtfilt, find_peaks
from scipy.interpolate import CubicSpline

def detect_r_peaks(ecg, fs=500):
    # Bandpass filter 0.5-40 Hz to remove baseline wander and high-frequency noise
    nyq = fs / 2
    b, a = butter(2, [0.5/nyq, 40/nyq], btype='band')
    filtered = filtfilt(b, a, ecg)
    # Simple peak detection with threshold
    peaks, _ = find_peaks(filtered, distance=fs*0.3, height=np.std(filtered)*0.5)
    return peaks

def rr_to_hrv(rr_times, fs_out=4):
    # rr_times: list of times of R peaks (seconds)
    rr_intervals = np.diff(rr_times)
    # Remove outliers (e.g., >20% deviation from median)
    median_rr = np.median(rr_intervals)
    rr_clean = rr_intervals[np.abs(rr_intervals - median_rr) / median_rr < 0.2]
    # Times for each RR interval (midpoints)
    t_rr = (rr_times[:-1] + rr_times[1:]) / 2
    t_rr = t_rr[np.abs(rr_intervals - median_rr) / median_rr < 0.2]
    # Cubic spline interpolation to uniform fs_out
    cs = CubicSpline(t_rr, rr_clean)
    t_uniform = np.arange(t_rr[0], t_rr[-1], 1/fs_out)
    hrv = cs(t_uniform)
    return t_uniform, hrv
```

